# Closed-loop dispatch state

Phase 2 of the "closed loop theme building" plan keeps the agent's
context fresh: a watchdog daemon (`bin/dispatch-watch.py`) snaps
themes whenever the source changes and writes a compact summary to
`tmp/dispatch-state.json`. **Read that file at the start of every turn
that touches a theme.** It tells you what the most recent snap saw
without forcing a fresh boot of `bin/snap.py shoot`.

## How to use

1. At the start of any turn that edits CSS / `theme.json` /
   `templates` / `parts` / `patterns`, open
   `@tmp/dispatch-state.json`. Treat its contents as ground truth for
   the visual state of the listed themes.
2. Look at `next_actions` first -- it's a pre-ranked list of the
   loudest fixes pending (per the remedy table in
   `bin/finding_remedies.json`). If `next_actions` is non-empty, work
   from it before snapping anything new.
3. Use `errors_by_route_viewport` to triage by route + viewport
   pair. Each entry includes `kind` (axe rule slug or DOM
   heuristic), `severity`, `message`, and `selector` -- enough to
   diagnose without re-reading the raw `findings.json`.
4. `last_run_at` (epoch seconds) tells you how stale the state is.
   If it's older than your last edit's mtime, the daemon hasn't seen
   your change yet -- give it the debounce window
   (`--debounce`, default 0.5s) plus the snap time, or run
   `python3 bin/snap.py shoot <theme>` once manually to refresh.
5. `last_dispatch_kind` is one of:
   - `noop` -- daemon just started, no snaps yet
   - `snap-only` -- a theme source file changed, daemon re-snapped
   - `overrides+snap` -- `bin/append-wc-overrides.py` itself
     changed, daemon re-ran the override generator THEN re-snapped
6. **Do not invent state when the file is missing.** If
   `tmp/dispatch-state.json` doesn't exist, the daemon isn't
   running. Either start it (`python3 bin/dispatch-watch.py
   --theme <slug>`) or accept that you'll be relying on whatever's
   in `tmp/snaps/<theme>/` from the previous shoot.

## Schema

```jsonc
{
  "schema": 1,
  "started_at": 1776860500,           // epoch when daemon started
  "last_run_at": 1776860590,          // epoch of most recent dispatch
  "last_dispatch_kind": "snap-only",  // noop|snap-only|overrides+snap
  "themes_dispatched": ["selvedge"],  // themes that triggered this run
  "themes_snapped": ["selvedge"],     // themes that completed shoot
  "errors_by_route_viewport": {
    "selvedge:checkout-filled:desktop": [
      {
        "theme": "selvedge",
        "route": "checkout-filled",
        "viewport": "desktop",
        "kind": "color-contrast",
        "severity": "error",
        "message": "Element has insufficient color contrast of 1.27...",
        "selector": ".wc-block-components-text-input label",
        "axe_help_url": "https://dequeuniversity.com/rules/axe/.../color-contrast"
      }
    ]
  },
  "suggested_fixes": [
    {
      "theme": "selvedge",
      "route": "checkout-filled",
      "viewport": "desktop",
      "axe_rule": "color-contrast",
      "selector": ".wc-block-components-text-input label",
      "remedy_id": "wc-input-contrast",
      "file": "bin/append-wc-overrides.py",
      "strategy": "boost specificity in CSS_PHASE_I",
      "example_diff": "..."
    }
  ],
  "next_actions": [
    "selvedge checkout-filled/desktop: color-contrast -> boost specificity in CSS_PHASE_I"
  ]
}
```

## When the daemon isn't running

Two valid recovery paths:

1. **Manual one-shot**: `python3 bin/dispatch-watch.py --once` runs a
   single dispatch cycle (debounce + snap) and exits. Re-reads
   `tmp/dispatch-state.json` afterwards.
2. **Long-running**: `python3 bin/dispatch-watch.py --theme <slug>`
   in a separate terminal. State refreshes automatically as you
   edit. Use `--no-snap` if Playground is wedged and you only want
   override-script reruns flowing.

## Related files

- `bin/dispatch-watch.py` -- the watcher daemon
- `bin/snap.py serve --shoot-on-demand` -- warm-server endpoint that
  the daemon talks to (Phase 2; ~3s/shot vs ~127s cold)
- `bin/finding_remedies.json` -- the (axe_rule, selector_pattern) ->
  (file, strategy, diff) table that powers `suggested_fixes` and
  `next_actions`
- `bin/check.py` -- the static gate that reads
  `tmp/snaps/<theme>/**/findings.json` directly during pre-commit
- `bin/fix-loop.py` -- the optional bracketing harness (3-attempt
  cap, hold-for-agent, structured failure report)
